lead_paragraph: Undeterred by the conflict triggered by Ukraine's swing towards Europe, the former Soviet republics of Moldova and Georgia will sign a trade and political pact with the European Union this month with Russia warning both countries against the move.

headline.main: Defying Russian Warnings, Moldova and Georgia Head for EU Pact
headline.print_headline: Defying Russian Warnings, Moldova and Georgia Head for EU Pact
